The paper deals with the classification of bird sounds using machine learning techniques. The most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), which deals with audio and speech processing. The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms, which makes cs.SI (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The proposed method involves the use of ensemble classifiers, which falls under cs.LG (Learning). The paper also deals with multi-label classification, which is a sub-topic of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
